snippet.textDisplay:
I don't understand why flat earthers obsess about NASA lying about the Earth being a globe.
NASA is just one of many space related bodies across the planet. I'm from India. We have ISRO here. NASA doesn't "tell" us whether or not the Earth is a globe.
Besides, the astronomical knowledge (including the Earth being spherical) is way older than NASA, which is only a few decades old.

Also, I find it rather frustrating when people just read something online and call it their "research". It just shows that people, in general, have no idea how much work goes into an actual research.
